    <Instrument_Host>
        <name>Venera 7</name>
        <type>Spacecraft</type>
        <description>

The Venera 7 spacecraft comprised a carrier bus holding a descent
craft/lander to study Venus. The carrier bus was designed to be a
communications relay for the lander and to explore interplanetary space
during cruise and Venus encounter. Instrumentation consisted of energetic
particle and solar wind detectors. Venera 7 was the first mission to return
data from the surface of another planet.

        </description>
